Description: dbf\_read\_iffy
        ===============
        
        Make possible to read from dbf's with codepage unsupported by modules
        dbf and codecs (895 cz Kamenicky, ..)
        
        ::
        
            import dbf
            from dbf_read_iffy import fix_init, fix_895
        
            fix_init(dbf)
            t = dbf.Table('autori.dbf')
            t.open('read-only')
            for record in t:
                print fix_895(record.autor)
            t.close()
        
        You can ignore Python 2.7 installation error in test\_v3.py (from aenum
        which is requirement of dbf).
        
        For 620 pl Mazovia: You can define conversion map in fix\_620(). If
        possible please: Fork me, clone your fork, commit/push, generate Pull
        request from your fork. Thx.
        
